This paper proposes a neural end-to-end system for Entity Linking (EL) that uses contextual similarity scores to jointly discover and link entities in a text document. EL is a task related to natural language processing and information extraction, which falls under the sub-categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also uses neural embeddings and a probabilistic mention-entity map, which are common techniques in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Neural Networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL, cs.AI, and cs.LG, followed by cs.IR and cs.NE.
